98. Surg Clin North Am. 2018 Aug;98(4):667-675. doi: 10.1016/j.suc.2018.03.003. Epub 2018 May 21.Screening Mammography: Recommendations and Controversies.Witten M(1), Parker CC(2).Author information: (1)Division of Surgical Oncology, The University of Alabama at Birmingham, FOT1138, 1720 2nd Avenue S, Birmingham, AL 35294-3411, USA. Electronic address:mwitten@uabmc.edu.(2)Division of Surgical Oncology, The University of Alabama at Birmingham, FOT1138, 1720 2nd Avenue S, Birmingham, AL 35294-3411, USA.Over the past several years, there have been numerous changes in the guidelinesfor screening mammography. Additionally, different societies have releasedguidelines with variance in the recommendations of age to initiate and frequency of imaging. The current recommendations as well as the importance of screeningmammography for early detection and survival are discussed.Published by Elsevier Inc.DOI: 10.1016/j.suc.2018.03.003 PMID: 30005766  [Indexed for MEDLINE]